    <item>
      <title>Sidlink: The Zonai</title>
      <author>antisthetic</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/603374</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/603374#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">6ee2c977c7dcb5629f76b2255059b0b55e1a6e50</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 27 Jun 2025 23:41:30 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/685f2986bafec.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/685f295e2f9f7.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6860b33a839c9.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6860b2f62f543.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6860b2f5e96f5.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6860b5be8008d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6860b5be920bf.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/685f2973445d6.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="SelectedElement"&gt;Welcome to the second release of the Sidlink series!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod wouldn't have become a thing without &lt;a href="https://kenneduck.tumblr.com/" target="_blank"&gt;Kenneduck&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href="https://www.tumblr.com/kenneduck/733295397674647552/secret-confessions-to-a-sage-masterpost?" target="_blank"&gt;Secret Confessions&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href="https://archiveofourown.org/users/Bitterlikesweets/profile" target="_blank"&gt;Bitterlikesweets&lt;/a&gt;' &lt;a href="https://archiveofourown.org/works/47382331" target="_blank"&gt;Untouchable Things&lt;/a&gt;. As well as Several other Sidlink things I've seen related to TOTK.&lt;br&gt;Also a thank you to &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/members/2233605"&gt;SpaceGeorge&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/452165"&gt;Princess-centric Loading Screen&lt;/a&gt; for inspiration for the save icon.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I highly recommend you use &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/512730"&gt;Complete Zonai Link&lt;/a&gt; AND/OR &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/496038"&gt;Zonai Link&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1722431"&gt;1722431&lt;/a&gt; otherwise this mod won't make much sense. But who am I to judge if you don't.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This dialogue edit currently edits various lines from NPCs to include the SidLink ship! It includes editing the progress of the Zora questline to include Sidon and Link's relationship and changing how they're referred to. However when I was making the original version of my personal project I noticed something that just felt odd with how I was playing... They kept referring to Link as a Hylian! I was often playing as Zonai Link at the time so I decided to fix that.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This version of the Sidlink mod makes various edits to the game outside of the Sidlink ship. Link will no longer be referred to as a Hylian.. But he won't be referred to as a Zonai either. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;With how the Zonai Link mod works, he's transformed because of his life being in jeopardy and the abilities of Rauru. In this case if he directly is being talked about as a Hylian, he's instead called a creature, unless being referred to as such in the past tense. Seeing as Zonai have been gone for a really long time, it makes sense that no one would call him one. The only one I could see calling him a Zonai is Tauro since he would DEFINITELY recognize Link as being one, seeing as he's dedicated his entire life to the research of them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Unfortunately I have yet to get the the modding level required to add new dialogue entries for Tauro and the NPCs he's around, as the dialogues are not separated by NPC most of the time but by Interaction. Once I get to that level I will release an update for this.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;But if you can plea your case for him being referred to as a Zonai by everyone, I'll consider releasing a separate file on this page for that version.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I recommend using the original Japanese audio with subtitles as I did alter subtitles for a line that Sidon says that removes the use of Link's name in the translation.&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Unless you are able to manually merge files yourself please use &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/TKMM-Team/TKMM/releases" target="_blank"&gt;TKMM&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. This mod won't be compatible with any other that edit the USen file otherwise.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;This was made with 1.2.1.&lt;br&gt;TKMM &lt;i&gt;may&lt;/i&gt; be able to merge it into different versions but I'm unsure, if that's not the case then I'll need to find a way to access different USen files but I don't have them currently.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If I missed anything or you have a suggestion for future updates or the other versions please let me know!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;u&gt;AI IS NEVER USED TO CREATE ANYTHING IN ANY OF MY MODS&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;ᶦᶠ ʸᵒᵘ ⁿᵒᵗᶦᶜᵉᵈ ᴵ ʳᵉᵘˢᵉᵈ ˢᶜʳᵉᵉⁿˢʰᵒᵗˢ.... ⁿᵒ ʸᵒᵘ ᵈᶦᵈⁿ'ᵗ&lt;br&gt;ᶦ'ˡˡ ᵘᵖˡᵒᵃᵈ ˢᵒᵐᵉ ᵐᵒʳᵉ ᶻᵒⁿᵃᶦ ˡᶦⁿᵏ ʳᵉˡᵃᵗᵉᵈ ᵒⁿᵉˢ ᶦⁿ ᵃ ᵇᶦᵗ, ᵗᵉᶜʰⁿᶦᶜᵃˡ ᵈᶦᶠᶠᶦᶜᵘˡᵗᶦᵉˢ ᵒⁿ ᵐʸ ᵉⁿᵈ, ᶦ ʲᵘˢᵗ ʷᵃⁿⁿᵃ ᵍᵉᵗ ᵗʰᵉ ᵐᵒᵈ ᵒᵘᵗ ᵗᵒⁿᶦᵍʰᵗ</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/sidlink-_zonai.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Text/Dialogue</category>
      <category>UI</category>
    </item>
