      <guid isPermaLink="false">feeea62efdde57cd98192e7696fc160efc6b73b5</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Jun 2025 14:54:17 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6464b80185057.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64623e203380d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64623e2029865.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; 1.0.0 and files/downloads&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;I had to dump the base game files for another reason, and figured I'd go ahead and make the mod compatible with v1.0.0. while I had it.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Since I had too many files, I decided to consolidate the separate downloads for each version into a single download which contains all the separate downloads I had before, rather than getting rid of some of them. Nothing else changed with the affected files. &lt;strong&gt;Keep in mind, however, that you should only use one of the three options if/when extracting a rocket file.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;Modified all the zonai devices to last a ridiculously long time. For reference, default wing time was 2250. It's now 5.4 million, along with everything else besides rockets and bombs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Take to the skies, my fellow Hylians.&lt;br&gt;Zonai Device Batteries are included. Link's batteries still work like normal.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Made rockets too. One doubled, and one for insanity. It doesn't last as long as the rest since it didn't like those values, but it's still a lot (90 vs 90000). Rockets don't last longer when attached to a shield. Sorry folks.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Removed the cooking pot from the main file. I forgot to remove it before I packaged it, and I was testing with the pot to see if I could make it stay after cooking, at least for 10 cooks, but no luck. That may have been the cause of some of the crashes. Luckily, someone else is working on that.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;br&gt;Now compatible with 1.0.0 too&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Let me know if there are any issues or if I missed anything.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Install Instructions:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Emulators: Right click TotK in the app and select the option to open the Mods folder/directory and extract, from the zip, the folder that contains romfs (folder with the name of the mod) into the directory. Be wary about mods/folders that contain the same files, as they will likely conflict.&lt;br&gt;Switch: Drop the romfs folder into your atmosphere\contents\0100F2C0115B6000 folder.&lt;br&gt;</description>
