    <item>
      <title>Unbreakable Equipment</title>
      <author>HylianLZ</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/443924</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/443924#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">ea791847be260a7eca718c00a2abe0b714866947</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Jun 2025 14:40:14 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64638f4b47e5e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64638f4a939fa.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Files/Downloads&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Since I had too many files, I decided to consolidate the separate downloads for each version into a single download which contains all the separate downloads I had before, rather than getting rid of some of them. Nothing else changed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Also reuploaded a few minutes later because I got rid of the "nested archives".&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;All swords, shields, spears, long swords, and bows are unbreakable. (Customizable by removing files from archive. See below) &lt;br&gt;Not dependent on Durability value. Affects all weapons that you get the files for, whether in inventory or freshly collected. Fusing an item to an unbreakable weapon doesn't affect the unbreakability. Everything you don't change with a weapon file works like normal.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;del&gt;Forgot to mod shield friction on my first run through the files, so now you have the option of making shields frictionless by using the other file and overwriting any from the main file that you want frictionless.&lt;/del&gt; When I did the update, I got rid of the non-frictionless version. It was never really my intention to make it without frictionless, because that's how I prefer it.&lt;del&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/del&gt;&lt;br&gt;Let me know if I missed anything. (If you ask nicely, I can also package a certain set of weapons together for you, like I did with the Master Sword and Hylian Shield)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Install Instructions:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Emulators: Right click TotK in the app and select the option to open the Mods folder/directory and extract, from the zip, the folder that contains romfs (folder with the name of the mod) into the directory. Be wary about mods/folders that contain the same files, as they will likely conflict.&lt;br&gt;Switch: Drop the romfs folder into your atmosphere\contents\0100F2C0115B6000 folder.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;If you don't want EVERYTHING to be unbreakable, you can pick and choose. &lt;br&gt;Click the link below.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vSqlaIbD9EuHM_dz0m81AYSDldqBPXnGLqLXjnHPdfTdgdIlUC5Ost2CqWhJS6CaSLotLRD2xXHJp7y/pubhtml" target="_blank"&gt;Equipment&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Champion Equipment zip includes: &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;Great Eagle Bow, Boulder Breaker, Daybreaker, Lightscale Trident, and Lightscale Trident.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Amiibo Equipment zip includes: &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;Sea-Breeze Boomerang, Sword of the Hero, White Sword of the Sky, Sea-Breeze Shield, Fierce Deity Sword, Dusk Claymore, Biggoron's Sword, and Dusk Bow.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Method&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;In pack\component\lifeparam, insert: "InitInvincibilityType: InvincibleNoDamageReaction, " before LifeParameters&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
